latestPosts.caption: ध्यान के प्रति AWARENESS  कैसे लेकर आएँ?

Hello all beautiful infinite beings 🌸
Welcome to SHUNIYA- seek within meditation 
This Sunday we bring to you Root Chakra Meditation 

Root chakra meditation is beneficial for anyone seeking grounding, stability, and a stronger sense of personal security. Here’s a breakdown of who should attend root chakra 
.
.
.
Ideal for People Who:
1. Feel Anxious, Fearful, or Insecure
• If someone often experiences fear, panic, or lack of safety (physical or emotional), this meditation can help them feel more rooted and stable.
2. Have Trouble with Focus or Staying
Present
• Root chakra meditations are grounding practices, ideal for individuals who feel scattered, distracted, or unproductive.
3. Are Going Through Major Life Changes
• People navigating transitions like job changes, relocations, breakups, or loss can benefit by restoring their inner foundation.
4. Struggle with Financial Stability
• Since the root chakra is linked with survival and security (including money), this meditation supports a more balanced mindset around abundance.
5. Feel Disconnected from Their Body
• Those who are always “in their head” or disconnected from physical sensations can benefit by reconnecting with their body and environment.
6. Want to Strengthen Self-Confidence
• A balanced root chakra builds inner strength, trust, and confidence, especially useful for people dealing with low self-worth.
7. Have Physical Issues in the Lower Body
• Anyone experiencing lower back pain, leg issues, or immune disorders may find energetic grounding beneficial (in complement to medical care).
• Specific Groups Who Benefit:
• Corporate professionals under stress
• Women rebuilding after trauma or major shifts
• Teenagers or young adults facing uncertainty
• Healers, coaches, and therapists who
needs grounding 
• Spiritual seekers working on energy balancing
• People with anxiety or trauma history
.
.
.
Its going to be fun charging out chakra and relaxing ourselves and be in communion with our Mother Earth 🌸🧿

Grateful for all the support and love ! 
Grateful for everyone having belief and faith in me and supporting SHUNYA - seek within 🌸🧿
Grateful to all the participants choosing it ! 
Received with gratitude 🌸
.
.
“Shunya,” meaning zero or emptiness, is a powerful concept in meditation and spiritual practice—symbolizing stillness, balance, and the infinite
.
.
Creating a meditation community like Shunya offers a deep space for growth—both individually and collectively
.
.
.
.
This time we did Chakra Meditation 
Chakra Meditation is a powerful practice that focuses on aligning and balancing the seven main energy centers in the body. These chakras are believed to influence physical, emotional, and spiritual well-being. Through focused awareness, breath, visualization, sound, or affirmations, you can activate and harmonize each chakra to promote inner balance.
We focused on chanting this time .
.
.
.
.
